77">
            <time datetime=3D"Sep 26, 2013, 6:16:26 PM" pubdate=3D"">
              2013-09-26
            </time>
          </a>

         =20
        </div>

        <div class=3D"body">
          <p>I=E2=80=99m pretty sure I found the issue. It=E2=80=99s in org=
.apache.cassandra.service.QueryState. It=E2=80=99s bad, but not <em>quite</=
em> as bad as you might think:</p>
<code class=3D"block">public long getTimestamp()
{
    long current =3D System.currentTimeMillis() * 1000;
    clock =3D clock &gt;=3D current ? clock + 1 : current;
    return clock;
}</code>
<p>The mistake is to not initialize current/clock with System.nanoTime(). I=
f that had been done it would avoid this problem, and frankly the code coul=
d have been simpler. There is obviously an attempt to avoid collisions for =
timestamps from the same node, but with multiple nodes this won=E2=80=99t r=
eally help.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

