        <div class=3D"body">
          <p>Is System.nanoTime() safe to call between threads/CPUs?  I bel=
ieve on x86 System.nanoTime() uses the TSC, which isn=E2=80=99t always sync=
ed properly between different cores and/or sockets on some implementations.=
  And System.currentTimeMillis() uses the wallclock?  It seems like you=E2=
=80=99d need something based on hardware like HPET to get the consistency o=
f timestamps you=E2=80=99re talking about.</p>

