            </time>
          </a>

         =20
        </div>

        <div class=3D"body">
          <p>Regarding timestamps: isn=E2=80=99t it the case that you=E2=80=
=99re constrained in precision by what the CPU can handle? The value return=
ed in a =E2=80=9Cnano-second=E2=80=9D timestamp may have misleading precisi=
on.</p>

<p>By which I mean, if you get 2 nano-second timestamps 1ns apart, they may=
