            <time datetime=3D"Apr 13, 2016, 12:18:39 PM" pubdate=3D"">
              2016-04-13
            </time>
          </a>

         =20
        </div>

        <div class=3D"body">
          <p>Since the Paxos algorithm rely on getting response from a Quor=
um of machine and the set of machine storing replica of a key might change =
at any-time, I think it could not possibly work.</p>

<p>As discussed in =E2=80=9Cpaxos made live=E2=80=9D paper Paxos algorithm =
itself could be used to implement group membership change, but this is not =
currently the case in Cassandra. </p>

<p>Also paxos assume storage is reliable and no dataloss is possible, in ca=
ssandra a machine could accept a proposal then crash and rejoin the ring wi=
th an empty state. This would break the paxos quorum requirement.</p>

<p>If I am wrong and Cassandra Paxos implemention have support for replica =
leaving and joining at runtime and dataloss on some node please let me know=
.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

